## The --done Input Challenge

Users should be able to say 'I've finished all of parsing' without listing every invariant ID. The expandDoneSet function accepts BOTH:
- Invariant IDs: 'APP-INV-001,APP-INV-015'
- Domain names: 'parsing' (expands to all invariants owned by the parsing domain)

```go
func expandDoneSet(db *sql.DB, specID int64, done []string, registry []storage.InvariantRegistryEntry) map[string]bool {
    doneSet := make(map[string]bool)
    domains := map[string]bool{}
    for _, d := range done {
        // Check if it's a domain name
        for _, r := range registry {
            if r.Domain == d { domains[d] = true }
        }
        if !domains[d] {
            doneSet[d] = true  // treat as invariant ID
        }
    }
    // Expand domains to invariant IDs
    for _, r := range registry {
        if domains[r.Domain] {
            doneSet[r.InvariantID] = true
        }
    }
    return doneSet
}
```

## Graph Duplication vs Shared Package

The progress package needs the same dependency graph as implorder. Rather than creating a shared 'graph' package (premature abstraction), duplicate the ~30 lines of graph construction. If a third consumer appears, THEN extract.

This follows the 'rule of three' for abstraction — don't abstract until you have three consumers.

